text: Jackson Hately (born 21 October 2000) is an Australian rules footballer who plays for the Greater Western Sydney in the Australian Football League (AFL). ==Early Career== Born in Canberra before growing up in Adelaide, Hately played 12 SANFL games for Central District in 2018 as a seventeen year old. He won All-Australian selection for his performances for South Australia in the NAB Under-18 National Championships. He was selected as a first round pick #14 in the 2018 national draft. ==AFL career== He made his senior debut against Fremantle in round 5 of the 2019 season.
